comments: LaVine (CHI) moves into Morant's (MEM) body and delivers contact that affects his driving shot attempt.

Adams (MEM) is moving alongside DeRozan's (CHI) path and legally contests the driving shot attempt. Any follow-through contact by Jackson Jr. (MEM) to DeRozan's body as they come together after the release is deemed marginal.
Adams (MEM) is already in LaVine's (CHI) path when contact occurs and he absorbs the contact to his upper body.
Anderson (MEM) briefly grasps White's (CHI) arm and marginal contact occurs as he dislodges the ball from LaVine (CHI).
Vucevic (CHI) clamps Anderson's (MEM) arm and restricts his ability to secure the rebound.
Vucevic (CHI) and Adams (MEM) come together at the same spot and marginal contact occurs off ball.
LaVine (CHI) steps slightly forward towards Morant (MEM) and marginal contact occurs at the end of the drive.
Adams (MEM) fails to fully clear the lane and is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
During the rebound, Adams (MEM) and Vucevic (CHI) mutually engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
LaVine (CHI) makes clean contact with the ball as he defends Jackson Jr.'s (MEM) drive.
Vucevic (CHI) cleanly dislodges the ball from Jackson Jr. (MEM).
DeRozan (CHI) and Jackson Jr. (MEM) each make clean contact with the ball as they tie each other up.  A jump ball is correctly called.
Adams (MEM) leans into Green's (CHI) path and delivers contact with his upper body.
Vucevic (CHI) legally contests Morant's (MEM) driving shot attempt and any follow-through contact with Morant's body after the release is deemed marginal.
Bane (MEM) swipes his hand down and makes contact with LaVine's (CHI) left arm as he defends the driving shot attempt.
During the screen, LaVine (CHI) and Morant (MEM) mutually engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
White (CHI) commits a take foul on Jones (MEM).
Anderson's (MEM) left hand makes clean contact with the ball as he cleanly dislodges the ball from DeRozan (CHI).
LaVine (CHI) commits a take foul on Morant (MEM).
All Technical Fouls are reviewed by League Operations.
